<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747157>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Dictuonia danae (d’Orbigny); Syntypes, MNHN R61520; Late Cretaceous, ‘Senonian’, Tours, Indre-et-Loire, France. (a) Bifoliate branch; (b) autozooids; (c) avicularium. (d) autozooids from another branch; (e) overall view of the same branch. Scale bars: a, e = 1 mm; b, c = 200 µm; d = 500 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4747157/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

